stimulus:
Several images will be presented sequentially. Each image will only be on the screen for about 100 milliseconds.

One of the images may be rotated 90 degrees right or left. Watch for this image and remember if it is rotated right or left.

Images of people and animals will appear, and sometimes they will be unpleasant. These will never be the rotated target image.
This is an example of an image rotated to the left.
This is an example of an image rotated to the right.

We will now begin a short practice session.

A + symbol will appear in the middle of the screen. Please fix your gaze on the center of the +, and then click the mouse button to begin the image sequence.

Please avoid blinking or eye movements while the images are on the screen.

The image sequence will start relatively slow. After a few sequences, it will speed up.

You have now completed the practice phase. We will now begin the real trials. This is a reminder that you will be searching for a rotated image among the series of upright images.

Remember, please do not blink or move your eyes while the images are on the screen.

At the end of the experiment, the experimenter will be able to show you how accurate you were.
This is your opportunity to take a break and rest your eyes.
